The `.htaccess` file is a configuration file used by Apache web servers. You can deny access based on IP addresses, user agents, or other criteria. Here’s an example of how to deny access to a specific IP address:

```apache
# Deny access to a specific IP
<RequireAll>
    Require all granted
    Require not ip 192.168.1.1
