### 3. **Using Nginx Configuration**

For Nginx servers, you can deny access by modifying the server block configuration. Here’s an example:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com;

    location / {
        deny 192.168.1.1;  # Deny access to this IP
        allow all;         # Allow all other IPs
    }
}
```

